<section class="section fade-up"><div class="container narrow stack-lg">
  <div class="figure" style="aspect-ratio: 4/3"><div class="placeholder" style="aspect-ratio: 4/3">[ portrait — Sara Leidelmeijer ]</div></div>
  <p class="t-lead t-pretty">Verdandi Weaver is the body of work of <strong>Sara Leidelmeijer</strong> — a writer, systemic thinker, and bridge-builder between science, spirit, nervous systems, and relational life.</p>
  <h2 class="t-h3">What this work is</h2>
  <p class="t-body t-pretty">A grounded approach to being human — including the soul, the nervous system, the body, the mind, identity, relationships, and the world they all live inside. A return rather than an escape.</p>
  <h2 class="t-h3">What it isn't</h2>
  <p class="t-body t-pretty">Not a transcendence project. Not a productivity stack. Not a fix. Wholeness begins when nothing in you is left out — including your tired parts, your doubt, your softness, and your quiet refusal.</p>
  <h2 class="t-h3">How it's offered</h2>
  <p class="t-body t-pretty">Through books, slow essays, gentle self-scans, visual frameworks, and — over time — circles and courses. Free where it can be, sustaining where it needs to be.</p>
  <span class="rule"></span>
  <p class="pull">You don't awaken out of being human. <em>You awaken into it.</em></p>
  <p class="t-meta center-text">Working from Sweden · in English &amp; Swedish.</p>
</div></section>
